metadata.name: Natural Cycles
metadata.description:
Every day we are kept alive.
Our hearts beat, our blood circulates, we breathe, and we desperately try to keep ourselves alive, even when we do not intend to. 
We live in such a miracle.
The earth is alive, too.
It is because it is alive that typhoons occur, and it rotates on its axis to maintain balance with the planet.
Perhaps the earth is trying to protect itself in order to protect human beings.

This world is a world where everything flows in cycles.
Time moves forward, emotions shift and change, and through circulation, they become clearer.

Loving oneself leads to loving the earth.
To love yourself is to love the earth, and to love the earth is to love yourself.
It is a wonderful cycle.

This work expresses that wonderful world.
We live together and grow together.

We will continue to care for the earth and engage in various activities.
I will engage in activities that are fun and full of happiness for both humans and the earth.
